Is there an eq bible out there that states: item x should be attainble at lvl y?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uyadensamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yaden Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(2/15/01 7:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://blackhole.cs.uwec.edu/~krauspa/claudus.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lvl 16 and lower</span><hr size=1> Don't worry too much about items up to 16. At 16 enchanters rock, so just do whatever you can to get up to that point. Mainly work on getting spells you need.<br>
<br>
Equipment to try to get as you get up to 16:<br>
<br>
Stein of Moggok (easy)<br>
Crude Stein (around 30pp i think)<br>
Jade Electrum Bracers<br>
<br>
...and eventually...<br>
<br>
Savants Cap (+3 int)<br>
Black Iron Medallion (+3 int)<br>
<br>
Just remember having a high INT isn't going to help you much until 20+ (or even 30+). Once I hit 25 I started to pay more attention on my INT and CHA. At that point money is better and you have more options.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps, I will happy to add more as I think of it. <p><hr><center><img src="http://blackhole.cs.uwec.edu/~krauspa/yaden.jpg"><BR><B><I>Yaden Samsara</B> Enchanter 34</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/udukemonty.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DukeMonty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(2/16/01 2:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks</span><hr size=1> Yes - it does help. Thanks. For my part, I have made 16 and by hunting the sisters I have been able to buy all the spells I need as well have around 40pp sitiing around. I have yet to quest for the stein - which I think is next but I have 2 important questions to ask:<br>
<br>
1) I had not read any posts on the enchanter class until around lvl 12 and am now coming to regret the fact that I created an Enchanter that follows Tunare. Without being Agnostic I have found that illusions are almost worthless. Should I dump this character?<br>
<br>
2) Okay, when I was walking through East Karana my pet attracted the attention of a few monsters. When they killed my pet, I tired to color flux/memblur them but I was always too busy being hit to have this work. How in the heck does an enchanter being chased by 2 mobs survive it? (note: I may have actually mem-blurred one of the prarie hounds, but standing close to it it just went instantly aggro again)<br>
<br>
Any insisghts on how we can live solo without begging for sows?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uvandaraadevitch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vandaraa DeVitch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(2/16/01 5:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> yes I would suggest you re-create your chanter with agnostic as your religion.  Getting to level 16 is not really a problem.  I had no help and I made it to 30 with just under 13 days played - so level 16 should be a snap <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Cheers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ufenaden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fenaden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=darkgreen>I am Jack's smirking revenge.</font></span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#330000>(2/17/01 10:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> well I'll have to agree with Vandaara on this one, I would re-create your character, but honestly I've made it to 50 and I'm not agnostic, but then again I'm not sure what religion I am LOL.  But it hasn't made a difference.  And my illusions are working great so far, only place I can't get into is Neriak after killing those guards and orcs in crushbone.  But if you feel that you won't have a hard time getting back to where you are I would say go ahead and re-create your character.  If not play with it and see what happens, I found out around 15ish or so and figured it'd be harder to re-create, so I didn't do it, but that was before I knew all the good hunting spots and there weren't hunting guides all over the net..<br>
