    -Elizabeth I</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/urafadelphi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rafa Delphi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#330000>(3/3/01 5:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> For the battle you were discribing you would have prevailed if you had tried using root.  What you would have needed to do was stun them both with Color Flux, then cast Root on one.  Back off and repeat.  Then once both are rooted you can then Memblur at your leasure. <p>Rafa Delphi <br>
32nd Erudite Enchanter <br>
"Order of Kynigos" <br>
Brell Serilis <br>
Master Baker, Brewer, <br>
Jeweler, Potter, Smith,<br>
