Guild Photographer <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/udellenneq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dellenn EQ</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#330000>(3/8/01 9:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/tonys22/boardpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks</span><hr size=1> Sure, you could do it that way with only a few sirens, however... the casting time is also a factor.  Flux is fast, you can easily cast it with two lightning fast sirens pounding on without an interrupt.  Also, you can get off a mez during that stun time which at least has a more reliable duration than root which oftentimes breaks with little or no warning catching you off guard; and I found root to be resisted more than mez in general.  Also, the spell regen cycle on mem blur is way too long to rely on root when battling two sirens.  If you have anything more than two mobs... I wouldn't advise doing that until you get AE memblur.  The thing about the sirens that is unique from say most other mobs is that they don't aggro, so in this case memblur could work.  If you were to try that at the LOIO against goblins all you would do is keep reaggroing yourself if you can't get out of range fast enough.  At least with mezing something and membluring you have a lot more time to either invis or just plain run for it.  Also, if it's a casting mob then root won't help you much. <p>Dellenn<BR>
42nd Dark Elf Enchanter<BR>
Blades of Law, Povar<BR>
